</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FD16FACC70ADC17929F3B01634163418" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="CAF84941D1BDEBE67803D3BA1D10C484" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ecology and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="09F8FA9230EB9F21E95AD06CDE81B471" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="9C36B651232B4D38DAE255D22EFFC165" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum praetermissum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="praetermissum">
<emphasis id="C70443AA70833172B88C3B03832EA7B3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum praetermissum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a plant of evergreen broadleaf forests or semi-deciduous forests, growing in forest understory or in clearings of secondary woodlands, or on rocky banks; from 300 to 400 m elevation.
</paragraph>
<caption id="8625B713DBFA270DECD7489A42978563" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.198.79514.figure54" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689747" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 54" startId="F54">
